<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 03 at 5:49PM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Showers with gusty winds and isolated thunderstorms will impact
southwest Virginia, southeast West Virgina and northwest North
Carolina through 630 PM EST...
At 546 PM EST, Doppler radar was tracking numerous showers and
isolated thunderstorms from Wilbar to Speedwell to Bluefield moving
northeast at 60 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Boone...
Radford...
Bluefield...
Mount Airy...
Pulaski...
Wytheville...
and Galax.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
